
[1]tremolite

   TREM'OLITE, n. A mineral, so called from Tremola, a valley in the Alps,
   where it was discovered. It is classed by Hauy with hornblend or
   amphibole, and called amphibole grammatite. It is of three kinds,
   asbestos, common, and glassy tremolite; all of a fibrous or radiated
   structure, and of a pearly color.

   Tremolite is a subspecies of straight edged augite.
